-- Israel Stocks: Givot Olam, Scailex, Electra Ltd. Are Active
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2012-01-30T11:00:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-30/israel-stocks-givot-olam-scailex-electra-ltd-are-active.html
Israel ’s  TA-25 Index (TA-25)  declined 0.5
percent to 1,115.65, the lowest intraday level since Jan. 25, at
12:37 p.m. in  Tel Aviv .  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Electra Ltd. (ELTR)  (ELTR IT) rose as much as 2.9 percent, before
trading 0.9 percent higher at 308.30 shekels. The manufacturer
of air-conditioning systems said a unit signed an agreement to
buy a 25 percent stake in a contender for a government contract
in the Negev. The Negev is Israel’s southern desert region.  Givot Olam Oil Exploration LP (GIVOL)   rose 7.4 percent
to 0.058 shekel, the highest intraday level since Dec. 20. The
Ministry of Energy & Water Resources approved the oil and gas
explorer’s development plan for the Meged field.  Scailex Corp. (SCIX)   rose 2.7 percent to 16.60 shekels,
the highest since Jan. 25. The importer and distributor of
mobile handsets said Chairman Ilan Ben-Dov bought 12,700 shares
in the company, lifting his ownership to 3.63 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in Tel Aviv at 
